-- Goldman Names Curtin to Replace Hodgson as Canada Banking Chief Executive
-- David Scanlan
-- 2010-06-29T21:07:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/goldman-names-curtin-to-replace-hodgson-as-canada-banking-chief-executive.html

          
          
             Goldman Sachs Group Inc. said it
named Jack Curtin as chief executive officer of its Canadian
unit, replacing Tim Hodgson, who is joining the Bank of Canada
as a special adviser to Governor Mark Carney. Goldman announced
Curtin’s appointment in a memo to staff today. Curtin was chief
executive of the bank’s Canadian unit from 1995 to 2000, and
joined the New York-based firm in 1976.  
          
          


  


        